body:
Hi Sarah,

Good news - no backend changes needed for override images!

## KISS Solution: Two-Step Flow

We already have `POST /api/events/upload-image` that does exactly what you need.

### Frontend Flow:

```javascript
// 1. Upload image first
const formData = new FormData();
formData.append('image', file);
formData.append('appId', appId);

const uploadRes = await fetch('/api/events/upload-image', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },
  body: formData
});
const { imageUrl } = await uploadRes.json();

// 2. Create override with the URL
await fetch(`/api/events/${eventId}/override`, {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: { 
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    instanceKey,
    overrideType: 'modify',
    patch: { overrideImage: imageUrl }
  })
});
```

### What upload-image returns:
```json
{ "success": true, "imageUrl": "https://tangotiempo.blob.core.windows.net/event-images/1/uuid-filename.jpg" }
```

